element_texts.text: Dear Jack, I am not exactly "like a bolt of lightning on it's holiday" (to quote a pretty fine author) when it comes to writing Thank you, but sooner or later I get around to it. I had a very enjoyable evening at your house, and was happy

to meet your wife and your other guests. I don't exactly remember the end of the evening, but I know I had a good time up to time I left. I'm getting a terrific bang from the book, Midland Humor, which you so graciously autographed for me. I'm sure Celia and
I will be seeing you around - perhaps at the College of Complexes. Sincerely, Trudy Hubbell Neubarth.
Can use a good fast one in this, Jack - just got it today - Best...Bill N.

typed In re: Harry Bridges: The Rise and Fall of Radical Labor in the U.S., by Charles P. Larrowe (Lawrence Hill) checked box Yea unchecked box Nay handwritten Yea, yea - Sorry for delay in Replying - just back from vacation - Holiday greetings - Bill Newman

7/17/86
Mr. "unsure" :
I was in the "unsure" with your son, Tom. In the same "unsure" at "unsure" Field in Kansas. 
He spoke of you often. He enjoyed "unclear" books which I "unclear" you "unclear" him. 
Now, I hope Tom is alive and well. And I would like to write to him.
Could you please send me his address?
I enclose a package paid, addressed envelope. Thanks, 
Boy "unclear"
